
[1]audit

   AUD'IT, n. [L. audit, he hears.]

   1. An examination of an account or of accounts, with a hearing of the
   parties concerned, by proper officers, or persons appointed for that
   purpose, who compare the charges with the vouchers, examine witnesses,
   and state the balance.

   2. The result of such an examination, or account as adjusted by
   auditors; a final account.

    AUD'IT, v.t. To examine and adjust an account or accounts, by proper
     officers, or by persons legally authorized for the purpose; as, to
      audit the accounts of a treasurer, or of parties who have a suit
                             depending in court.
